    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"432410\">@Arthur Adjedj</span> mentioned that if I give a name to the <code>LE</code> instance and provide the name to <code>grind</code>, then the proof finishes properly. Therefore, I can just add a <code>@[grind =]</code> attribute to the <code>instance</code> definition and the proof goes by. But I still need to specify <code>LE.le</code>.</p>",
        "id": 563246924,
        "sender_full_name": "Ayhon",
        "timestamp": 1765474294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, that actually makes sense, because <code>LE.le</code> only unfolds if the instance argument is a constructor, and for it to be a constructor the instance also needs to unfold. But maybe it'd be nice to always unfold instances?</p>",
